        <definition>const PinRef PIN_NC</definition>
        <argsstring></argsstring>
        <name>PIN_NC</name>
        <briefdescription>
<para>No-connect sentinel. Pass where no physical pin exists. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>All reads return false / 0; all writes are no-ops. Provided as a named constant for readability in wiring maps.</para>
<para>Usage: <computeroutput><ref refid="classPinRef" kindref="compound">PinRef</ref> pins[] = { <ref refid="classPinRef" kindref="compound">PinRef(exp1, PORT_A, 0)</ref>, PIN_NC, <ref refid="classPinRef" kindref="compound">PinRef(exp1, PORT_A, 2)</ref> };</computeroutput></para>
<para>See also: ANALOG_NC (0xFFFF) for AnalogMultiPos unused voltage levels. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
